            [WARNING] On Nov 22, 2018 this sequence was replaced by
            NP_000517.3.
            
            On Sep 5, 2001 this sequence version replaced NP_000517.1.
            
            Summary: This gene encodes a member of the keratin family, the most
            diverse group of intermediate filaments. This gene product, a type
            I keratin, is usually found as a heterotetramer with two keratin 5
            molecules, a type II keratin. Together they form the cytoskeleton
            of epithelial cells. Mutations in the genes for these keratins are
            associated with epidermolysis bullosa simplex. At least one
            pseudogene has been identified at 17p12-p11. [provided by RefSeq,
            Jul 2008].
            
            Publication Note:  This RefSeq record includes a subset of the
            publications that are available for this gene. Please see the Gene
            record to access additional publications.
            
